<p>
  {gettext(
    "BotService lets you create and manage extensible bots that live in channels, respond to messages, greet users, and execute custom commands. Bots are built on a pluggable capability system — each bot can be configured with different behaviors."
  )}
</p>

<.help_h4 icon={:icon_wrench}>{gettext("Capabilities")}</.help_h4>
<p>{gettext("Each bot can have one or more capabilities enabled:")}</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>{gettext("Mentions")}</strong> {gettext(
      "— responds when someone mentions the bot by name"
    )}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{gettext("Greeter")}</strong>
    {gettext("— welcomes users when they join a channel, optionally says goodbye on part")}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{gettext("Custom Commands")}</strong>
    {gettext("— user-defined")} <code>{gettext("!BotName trigger")}</code>
    {gettext("commands with configurable responses")}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{gettext("Help")}</strong>
    {gettext("— built-in")} <code>{gettext("!BotName help")}</code>
    {gettext("command that lists available commands")}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{gettext("Dice")}</strong>
    {gettext("— RPG dice rolling with standard notation (")}<code>2d6</code>, <code>{gettext("d20+5")}</code>, <code>4d6kh3</code>{gettext(
      "). Use"
    )} <code>{gettext("!BotName roll <notation>")}</code>
    {gettext("to roll dice")}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{gettext("Moderation")}</strong>
    {gettext(
      "— auto-moderation that monitors all messages for blocked words, spam, flood, and caps lock abuse. Configurable actions: warn, mute, or kick"
    )}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{gettext("Trivia")}</strong> {gettext(
      "— interactive quiz with 6 categories, scoring, and timers. Use"
    )} <code>{gettext("!BotName trivia start")}</code> {gettext("to begin a round")}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{gettext("Scheduler")}</strong> {gettext(
      "— posts scheduled/periodic messages to channels. Supports interval (every N minutes) and daily (at HH:MM UTC) schedules"
    )}
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>{gettext("RSS")}</strong> {gettext(
      "— monitors RSS/Atom feeds and posts new items to channels. Use"
    )} <code>{gettext("!BotName rss add <url> <#channel>")}</code> {gettext("to add a feed")}
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  {gettext("Additional capabilities (LLM, Script, Game) are planned for future releases.")}
</p>

<.help_h4 icon={:icon_tab_control}>{gettext("How Bots Work")}</.help_h4>
<p>
  {gettext(
    "Each bot runs as its own process on the server. When a message arrives in a channel the bot has joined, the bot checks each capability in order. Passive capabilities (like Moderation) run on every message, while active capabilities use first-match-wins. A cooldown timer prevents the bot from responding too frequently."
  )}
</p>
<p>
  {gettext("Bots appear in the channel nicklist with a")} <strong>⚙</strong>
  {gettext(
    "prefix and are grouped below regular users. They can be kicked or banned from channels like normal users."
  )}
</p>

<.help_h4 icon={:icon_shield}>{gettext("Permissions")}</.help_h4>
<p>
  {gettext("Only")} <strong>admins</strong>
  and <strong>{gettext("server operators")}</strong>
  {gettext(
    "can create, modify, or delete bots. All users can view bot info and use bot commands."
  )}
</p>

<.help_h4 icon={:icon_dice}>{gettext("Dice Notation")}</.help_h4>
<p>{gettext("The Dice capability supports standard RPG notation:")}</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <code>{gettext("NdS")}</code> {gettext("— roll N dice with S sides (e.g.,")} <code>2d6</code>)
  </li>
  <li>
    <code>{gettext("dS")}</code> {gettext("— shorthand for 1 die (e.g.,")} <code>d20</code>)
  </li>
  <li>
    <code>{gettext("NdS+M")}</code> {gettext("— add modifier (e.g.,")} <code>{gettext("d20+5")}</code>)
  </li>
  <li>
    <code>{gettext("NdS-M")}</code> {gettext("— subtract modifier (e.g.,")} <code>d8-2</code>)
  </li>
  <li>
    <code>{gettext("NdSkhK")}</code> {gettext("— keep highest K dice (e.g.,")} <code>4d6kh3</code>)
  </li>
  <li>
    <code>{gettext("NdSklK")}</code> {gettext("— keep lowest K dice (e.g.,")} <code>2d20kl1</code>)
  </li>
</ul>

<.help_h4 icon={:icon_question}>{gettext("Trivia Categories")}</.help_h4>
<p>
  {gettext(
    "Available trivia categories: general, science, history, geography, technology, entertainment."
  )}
</p>
<p>
  {gettext("Commands:")} <code>{gettext("!Bot trivia start")}</code>, <code>{gettext("!Bot trivia stop")}</code>, <code>{gettext("!Bot trivia score")}</code>,
  <code>{gettext("!Bot answer <text>")}</code>
</p>

<.help_h4 icon={:icon_code}>{gettext("Template Placeholders")}</.help_h4>
<p>{gettext("Bot responses support these placeholders:")}</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>{"{nickname}"}</code> {gettext("— the user who triggered the response")}</li>
  <li><code>{"{channel}"}</code> {gettext("— the current channel name")}</li>
  <li><code>{"{topic}"}</code> {gettext("— the current channel topic")}</li>
  <li>
    <code>{"{prefix}"}</code> {gettext("— the bot's command prefix (e.g.,")} <code>!</code>)
  </li>
  <li><code>{"{botname}"}</code> {gettext("— the bot's display name")}</li>
</ul>

<.help_h4 icon={:icon_laptop}>{gettext("Management Dialog")}</.help_h4>
<p>
  {gettext("Open the Bot Management dialog from the")} <strong>{gettext("Tools")}</strong>
  {gettext("menu or by typing")} <code>{gettext("/bot")}</code>
  {gettext(
    "with no arguments (admin only). The dialog shows all bots with a split-view: select a bot on the left to see its details, channels, commands, and event hooks on the right."
  )}
</p>

<.help_h4 icon={:icon_link}>{gettext("See Also")}</.help_h4>
<p>
  <.help_link topic="bot-command">{gettext("/bot Command Reference")}</.help_link>
  · <.help_link topic="bot-custom-commands">{gettext("Bot Custom Commands")}</.help_link>
  · <.help_link topic="bot-dice">{gettext("Dice")}</.help_link>
  · <.help_link topic="bot-trivia">{gettext("Trivia")}</.help_link>
  · <.help_link topic="bot-scheduler">{gettext("Scheduler")}</.help_link>
  · <.help_link topic="bot-rss">{gettext("RSS")}</.help_link>
  · <.help_link topic="bot-moderation">{gettext("Moderation")}</.help_link>
  · <.help_link topic="chanserv">{gettext("ChanServ")}</.help_link>
</p>
